This device uses an FTDI serial-to-USB chip. If your device isn't found install [drivers](https://www.ftdichip.com/Drivers/VCP.htm).

Download custom compiled [tasmota32-lvgl.bin](https://github.com/Jason2866/Tasmota/blob/firmware/firmware/tasmota32/tasmota32-lvgl.bin).

Download [ST7735S_M5StickC_display.ini](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/arendst/Tasmota/development/tasmota/displaydesc/ST7735S_M5StickC_display.ini), rename to **display.ini** and upload using *Consoles - File Upload* menu.

Next, download [axp192.be](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/arendst/Tasmota/development/tasmota/berry/drivers/axp192.be) and upload using *Consoles - File Upload* menu.

Use the examples in this [GitHub discussion](https://github.com/arendst/Tasmota/discussions/11784) to use the display.